<paragraph id="8BADEB13EA43FFE6F2A6FB2C03D1AE98" blockId="20.[1710,2027,1196,1225]" box="[1710,2027,1196,1225]" pageId="20" pageNumber="133">Late Maastrichtian</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADEB13EA43FFE6F196FB73026AAFA2" blockId="20.[1337,2400,1263,2654]" pageId="20" pageNumber="133">
Several tyrannosaurids have been documented in Late Maastrichtian sediments of western North America, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F131FACA031AAF35" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1337,1824,1352,1390]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cf. A. mirandus">Aublysodon cf. A. mirandus</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F349FAC50D72AF34" author="Molnar, R. E. &amp; Carpenter, K." box="[1857,2376,1351,1390]" firstAuthor="Molnar" journalOrPublisher="Geobios" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="445 - 454" part="22" refId="ref18439" refString="Molnar, R. E. and Carpenter, K., 1989, The Iordan theropod (Maastrichtian, Montana, U. S. A.) referred to the genus Aublysodon: Geobios, v. 22, p. 445 - 454." title="The Iordan theropod (Maastrichtian, Montana, U. S. A.) referred to the genus Aublysodon" type="journal article" year="1989">Molnar and Carpenter, 1989</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F132FAF602A7AFC0" baseAuthorityName="Gilmore" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[1338,1693,1396,1425]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Albertosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cf. A. lancensis">Albertosaurus lancensis</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F2BBFAF603B8AFC0" author="Molnar, R. E." box="[1715,1922,1396,1432]" firstAuthor="Molnar" journalOrPublisher="Iournal of Paleontology" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="102 - 108" part="54" refId="ref18406" refString="Molnar, R. E., 1980, An albertosaur from the Hell Creek Formation of Montana: Iournal of Paleontology, v. 54, p. 102 - 108." title="An albertosaur from the Hell Creek Formation of Montana" type="book chapter" year="1980">Molnar, 1980</bibRefCitation>
) (= 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F3B1FAF10D72AFC0" authorityName="Paul" authorityYear="1988" box="[1977,2376,1395,1434]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Albertosaurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="megagracilis">
A. megagracilis 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6FCADFAF10D72AFC0" author="Paul, G. S." bookContentInfo="464 p." box="[2213,2376,1395,1429]" firstAuthor="Paul" journalOrPublisher="Simon and Schuster, New York" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" refId="ref18768" refString="Paul, G. S., 1988, Predatory Dinosaurs of the World: AComplete Illustrated Guide. Simon and Schuster, New York, 464 p." title="Predatory Dinosaurs of the World: AComplete Illustrated Guide" type="book" year="1988">Paul, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F18CFA22029AAFEB" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1905" box="[1412,1696,1440,1478]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Tyrannosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rex">Tyrannosaurus rex</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F2B1FA2203AAAFEC" author="Osborn, H. F." box="[1721,1936,1440,1475]" firstAuthor="Osborn" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="259 - 265" part="21" refId="ref18545" refString="Osborn, H. F., 1905, Tyrannosaurus and other Cretaceous carnivorous dinosaurs: Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, v. 21, p. 259 - 265." title="Tyrannosaurus and other Cretaceous carnivorous dinosaurs" type="book chapter" year="1905">Osborn, 1905</bibRefCitation>
). All but 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6FC25FA220CBBAFEB" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1905" box="[2093,2177,1440,1467]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Tyrannosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="138" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rex">T. rex</taxonomicName>
are problematic assignments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADEB13EA43FFE6F194FA740D35A2F1" blockId="20.[1337,2400,1263,2654]" pageId="20" pageNumber="133">
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F194FA740324AC43" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1436,1822,1526,1565]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirandus">Aublysodon mirandus</taxonomicName>
was the name restricted to a nondenticulate premaxillary tooth by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F3B2F9A00CA8AC15" author="Marsh, O. C." box="[1978,2194,1570,1606]" firstAuthor="Marsh" journalOrPublisher="American Iournal of Science" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="449 - 453" part="43" refId="ref18292" refString="Marsh, O. C., 1892, Notice of new reptiles from the Laramie Formation; American Iournal of Science, v. 43, p. 449 - 453." title="Notice of new reptiles from the Laramie Formation" type="journal article" year="1892">Marsh (1892)</bibRefCitation>
included in the type series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F26DF9CC0C5EAC21" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1856" box="[1637,2148,1613,1652]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Deinodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horridus">
Deinodon horridus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F3A9F9CC0C61AC3A" author="Leidy, J." box="[1953,2139,1614,1652]" firstAuthor="Leidy" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences Philadelphia" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="72 - 73" part="8" refId="ref17997" refString="Leidy, J., 1856, Notice of remains of extinct reptiles and fishes, discovered by Dr. F. V. Hayden in the badlands of the Judith River, Nebraska Territory; Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences Philadelphia, ' v. 8, p. 72 - 73." title="Notice of remains of extinct reptiles and fishes, discovered by Dr. F. V. Hayden in the badlands of the Judith River, Nebraska Territory" type="journal article" year="1856">Leidy, 1856</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6FD2DF9CC01D5ACCD" author="Osborn, H. F." firstAuthor="Osborn" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="259 - 265" part="21" refId="ref18545" refString="Osborn, H. F., 1905, Tyrannosaurus and other Cretaceous carnivorous dinosaurs: Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, v. 21, p. 259 - 265." title="Tyrannosaurus and other Cretaceous carnivorous dinosaurs" type="book chapter" year="1905">Osborn (1905)</bibRefCitation>
abandoned 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F2BFF9FB0356ACCF" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1719,1900,1657,1695]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F377F9FB0CB1ACCC" author="Carpenter, K." box="[1919,2187,1657,1695]" firstAuthor="Carpenter" journalOrPublisher="University of Wyoming, Contributions in Geology" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="123 - 134" part="20" refId="ref16427" refString="Carpenter, K., 1982, Baby dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous Lance and Hell Creek formations and a description of a new species of theropod: University of Wyoming, Contributions in Geology, v. 20, p. 123 - 134." title="Baby dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous Lance and Hell Creek formations and a description of a new species of theropod" type="book" year="1982">Carpenter (1982)</bibRefCitation>
rediagnosed 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F132F92602BEAC91" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1338,1668,1700,1738]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirandus">Aublysodon mirandus</taxonomicName>
based on new teeth collected in Lancian sediments of Wyoming. Since then, one partial skull (
<materialsCitation id="3B7AE14EEA43FFE6FC71F9520D6AACBD" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3396372306" box="[2169,2384,1744,1773]" collectionCode="LACM" httpUri="https://collections.nhm.org/dinosaur-institute/Display.php?irn=1032652&amp;QueryPage=%2Fdinosaur-institute%2F&amp;BackRef=ResultsList.php " pageId="20" pageNumber="133" specimenCode="LACM 28471">LACM 28471</materialsCitation>
) from late Maastrichtian beds of Montana has been referred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F132F8A502D1AD14" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1338,1771,1831,1869]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cf. A. mirandus">Aublysodon cf. A. mirandus</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F322F8A50D33AD1B" author="Molnar, R. E. &amp; Carpenter, K." box="[1834,2313,1831,1870]" firstAuthor="Molnar" journalOrPublisher="Geobios" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="445 - 454" part="22" refId="ref18439" refString="Molnar, R. E. and Carpenter, K., 1989, The Iordan theropod (Maastrichtian, Montana, U. S. A.) referred to the genus Aublysodon: Geobios, v. 22, p. 445 - 454." title="The Iordan theropod (Maastrichtian, Montana, U. S. A.) referred to the genus Aublysodon" type="journal article" year="1989">Molnar and Carpenter (1989)</bibRefCitation>
who expanded the diagnosis of the taxon to include skeletal material for the first time. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F2CCF8FD0C89ADF2" author="Lehman, T. M. &amp; K. Carpenter" box="[1732,2227,1918,1958]" firstAuthor="Lehman" journalOrPublisher="Iournal of Paleontology" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="1026 - 1032" part="64" refId="ref17955" refString="Lehman, T. M. and K. Carpenter, 1990, A partial skeleton of the tyrannosaurid dinosaurAublysadan from the Upper Cretaceous of New Mexico: Iournal of Paleontology, v. 64, p. 1026 - 1032." title="A partial skeleton of the tyrannosaurid dinosaurAublysadan from the Upper Cretaceous of New Mexico" type="journal article" year="1990">Lehman and Carpenter (1990)</bibRefCitation>
referred a partial skeleton (OMNH 10131; 
<figureCitation id="1329F796EA43FFE6F34EF82E0395AD97" box="[1862,1967,1963,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Daspletosaurus sp. (OMNH 10131) from the upper Fruitland or Kirtland (exclusive of Naashoibito Member) formations. Left postorbital in A, lateral, B, caudal, C, medial, and D, dorsal views; frontoparietal region in E, dorsal, F, ventral, G, right lateral, and H, rostral views; partial left dentary in I, lateral, and I, medial views; left femur in K, proximal, L, rostral, M, medial, N, caudal, and O, lateral views; right femur in P, proximal, Q, rostral, R, medial, S, lateral, and T, caudal views; distal half of right tibia in U, rostral, V, medial, W, lateral, and X, caudal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373665/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" targetBox="[349,2270,320,2766]" targetPageId="6">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329F796EA43FFE6F3CAF82E0C23AD97" box="[1986,2073,1964,1991]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Daspletosaurus sp. (ONINH 10131) from the upper Fruitland or Kirtland (exclusive of Naashoibito Member) formations. Right metatarsal H in A, rostral, D, distal, E, lateral, G, caudal, and I, medial views; right metatarsal HI in B, rostral, C, distal, F, lateral, and I JI, medial views; K, various ribs in rostral and caudal views. L-Q NMIVINH P250891, indeterminate tyrannosaurid femur from the De-na-zin Member of the Kirtland Formation in L, rostral, M, medial, N, proximal, O, caudal, P, distal, and Q, lateral views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373667/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" targetBox="[339,2256,350,2803]" targetPageId="7">6A-K</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329F796EA43FFE6FC24F82E0CBCAD9C" box="[2092,2182,1963,1996]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionText="FIGURE 10. Tyrannosaurid skull bones. A-I, Daspletosaurus sp. (OMNH 10131), with left postorbital in A, lateral, B, dorsal, and C, caudal views; frontoparietal region in D, dorsal, E, ventral, F, right lateral, and G, left lateral views; and left dentary in H, medial and I, lateral views. I-M, Tyrannosaurus rex (NMMNH P-3698), with vomerine process of rightpalatine in], medial, and L, lateral views; and basal portion in K, medial and M, lateral views. Scale bars equal 10 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373675/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" targetBox="[227,2413,225,3029]" targetPageId="12">10A-I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329F796EA43FFE6FC91F8290D3DAD9C" box="[2201,2311,1963,1996]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Comparison of tyrannosaurid femora. A-F, P-22976, right femur in A, lateral, B, medial, C, rostral, D, caudal, E, proximal, and F, distal views. G-L, P—25083, right femur in G, lateral, H, medial, I, rostral, I, caudal, K, proximal, and L, distal views. M-U, OMNH 10131, right femur in M, lateral, O, medial, Q, roslral, S, caudal, and V, proximal views; left femur in N, lateral, P, medial, R, rostral, T, caudal, and U, proximal views. Scale bar equals 10 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373679/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" targetBox="[138,2329,242,3050]" targetPageId="15">11M-U</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329F796EA43FFE6FD12F82E0172ADA2" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionText="FIGURE 12. Comparison of tyrannosaurid tibiae. A-E NMMNH P-25085, right tibia in A, lateral, B, medial, C, rostral, D, caudal, and E, proximal views. F-I OMNH 10131, distal end of right tibia in F, rostral, G, caudal, H, lateral, and I medial views. Scale bar equals 10 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373677/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" targetBox="[224,2404,239,2082]" targetPageId="16">12F- I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329F796EA43FFE6F152F85A0188ADA9" box="[1370,1458,2007,2042]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionText="FIGURE 13. Comparison of tyrannosaurid metatarsals. A-J, OMNH 10131, right metatarsal II in A, rostral, C, caudal, E, medial, G, lateral, and J, distal views; metatarsal III in B, rostral, D, caudal, F, medial, H, lateral, and I distal views. K-O, NMMNH P—25049, right metatarsus in K, rostral, L, lateral, M caudal N medial and O, distal views. Scale bars in I and J equal 5 cm, all others equal 10 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373681/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" targetBox="[150,2348,231,2615]" targetPageId="17">13A- J</figureCitation>
) from late Campanian strata of New Mexico to 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6FCA3F8540211A273" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cf. A. mirandus">Aublysodon cf. A. mirnndus</taxonomicName>
, and expanded the skeletal diagnosis. As demonstrated above, the latter specimen is referable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6FC64F7AF0D6EA203" authorityName="Russell" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Carr and Williamson" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[2156,2388,2093,2131]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Daspletosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Daspletosaurus</taxonomicName>
. The referral of the skeletal material to 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F3CDF7DB0C43A22F" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1989,2169,2137,2175]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
in both cases was based on associated nondenticulate premaxillary teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADEB13EA43FFE7F197F7330587AF8E" blockId="20.[1337,2400,1263,2654]" lastBlockId="21.[151,1218,1428,3037]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="134" pageId="20" pageNumber="133">
More recently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F29AF7320372A286" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1682,1864,2224,2262]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
teeth have been documented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F135F75E0253A2AF" author="Currie, PJ &amp; Rigby, JK. Jr. &amp; Sloan, RE" box="[1341,1641,2268,2303]" editor="Carpenter, K. &amp; Currie, PJ." etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Currie" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge, Cambridge University Press" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="107 - 125" refId="ref16971" refString="Currie, PJ., Rigby, JK. Jr. and Sloan, RE., 1990, Theropod teeth from the Judith River Formation; in Carpenter, K. and Currie, PJ., eds., Dinosaur Systematics: Cambridge, Cambridge University Press, p. 107 - 125." title="Theropod teeth from the Judith River Formation" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Dinosaur Systematics" year="1990">Currie et al. (1990)</bibRefCitation>
from the Dinosaur Park Formation. They also note identical teeth from the Iren Dabasu Formation in the People's Republic of China that might be derived from 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6FC1CF6B00CDEA31E" authority="Gilmore, 1933" authorityName="Gilmore" authorityYear="1933" box="[2068,2276,2354,2382]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Alectrosaurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Alectrosaurus</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6FCFEF6B001DCA32B" author="Currie, PJ &amp; Rigby, JK. Jr. &amp; Sloan, RE" editor="Carpenter, K. &amp; Currie, PJ." etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Currie" journalOrPublisher="Cambridge, Cambridge University Press" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="107 - 125" refId="ref16971" refString="Currie, PJ., Rigby, JK. Jr. and Sloan, RE., 1990, Theropod teeth from the Judith River Formation; in Carpenter, K. and Currie, PJ., eds., Dinosaur Systematics: Cambridge, Cambridge University Press, p. 107 - 125." title="Theropod teeth from the Judith River Formation" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Dinosaur Systematics" year="1990">Currie et al., 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F200F6DD0304A3D1" author="Eaton, J. G. &amp; Diem, S. &amp; Archibald, J. D. &amp; Schierup, C. &amp; Munk, H." box="[1544,1854,2398,2434]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Eaton" journalOrPublisher="Utah Geological Survey, Miscellaneous Publication" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="323 - 353" part="99 - 1" refId="ref17081" refString="Eaton, J. G., Diem, S., Archibald, J. D., Schierup, C. and Munk, H., 1999 a, Vertebrate paleontology of the Upper Cretaceous Rocks of the Markagunt Plateau, southwestern Utah: Utah Geological Survey, Miscellaneous Publication 99 - 1, p. p. 323 - 353" title="Vertebrate paleontology of the Upper Cretaceous Rocks of the Markagunt Plateau, southwestern Utah" type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">Eaton et al. (1999 a)</bibRefCitation>
reported ”? 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6FC0CF6DF0C83A3D3" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[2052,2233,2397,2435]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
sp. ” from a Santonian locality in southwestern Utah, although the nature of the material is not indicated. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6F342F6340CA1A388" author="Eaton, J. G. &amp; Cifelli, R. L. &amp; Hutchison, J. H. &amp; Kirkland, J. I. &amp; M. Parrish" box="[1866,2203,2484,2520]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Eaton" journalOrPublisher="Utah Geological Survey, Miscellaneous Publica- tion" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="323 - 353" part="99 - 1" refId="ref17145" refString="Eaton, J. G., Cifelli, R. L., Hutchison, J. H., Kirkland, J. I. and]. M. Parrish, 1999 b, Cretaceous vertebrate faunas from the Kaiparowits Plateau, south-central Utah: Utah Geological Survey, Miscellaneous Publication 99 - 1, p. 323 - 353" title="Cretaceous vertebrate faunas from the Kaiparowits Plateau, south-central Utah" type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="b">Eaton et al. (1999b)</bibRefCitation>
report ” cf. 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F134F66301D5A057" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1340,1519,2529,2567]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
sp. from the middle to late Turonian Smoky Hollow Member of the Straight Cliffs Formation of Utah (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8396E2EA43FFE6FC7FF5890D73A078" author="Parrish, J. M." box="[2167,2377,2571,2607]" firstAuthor="Parrish" journalOrPublisher="Utah Geological Survey, Miscellaneous Publication" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" pagination="329 - 321" part="99 - 1" refId="ref18729" refString="Parrish, J. M., 1999, Dinosaur teeth from the Upper Cretaceous (Turonian-Judithian) of southern Utah: Utah Geological Survey, Miscellaneous Publication 99 - 1, p. 329 - 321." title="Dinosaur teeth from the Upper Cretaceous (Turonian-Judithian) of southern Utah" type="book" year="1999">Parrish, 1999</bibRefCitation>
). These occurrences give 
<taxonomicName id="4C129090EA43FFE6F2C2F5B50345A00D" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1868" box="[1738,1919,2615,2653]" class="Reptilia" family="Tyrannosauridae" genus="Aublysodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dinosauria" pageId="20" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Aublysodon</taxonomicName>
a maximum temporal range of 26 million years in North America, an unprecedented duration among dinosaurs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF6DBB9BEA42FFE7F49DFB6307F4AF1B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4033145" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4033145" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4033145/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="134" startId="21.[149,272,1249,1273]" targetBox="[148,2326,204,1224]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="8BADEB13EA42FFE7F49DFB6307F4AF1B" blockId="21.[149,2322,1245,1365]" pageId="21" pageNumber="134">FIGURE 16. Examples of tyrannosaurid caudal vertebrae. A-D, NMMNH P-27287, proximal caudal vertebra in A, right lateral, and B, left lateral caudal vertebra in C, lateral and D, left lateral views. E-F, NMMNH P-28923, distal caudal vertebra in E, left lateral and F, lateral views. Scale bar equals 10 cm in A-D; 5 cm in E-F.</paragraph>
